  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Continue Supporting Brazil to Mitigate the Impact and Consequences of COVID-19 Spread and Increase Resilience of Vulnerable Brazilian</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM will continue supporting the Brazilian response to COVID-19 to mitigate its impact on the Brazilian vulnerable populations living in the states of Roraima (RR), Amazonas (AM) and Par&#xE1; (PA). In line with IOM&#x2019;s global Strategic Response and Recovery Plan / COVID-19 for 2021, the project will support existing health care facilities and health care professionals with capacity building activities and strengthened coordination and ensure the provision of primary health care services and mental health and psychosocial support. The project will improve access to water, sanitation and hygiene items and services and enhance infection prevention and control in the selected areas of intervention. The project will also raise awareness on the risks associated with the pandemic and empower community leaders to play an active role against the spread of COVID-19 through a Risk Communication and Community Engagement strategy.</narrative>
  </description>
